A businesswoman has denied threatening to kill her pregnant neighbour.Ndunge Koti, 27, is accused of abusing Janet Kerubo and saying she would kill her unborn child after they fought over who would fetch water first at a tap in their compound.The offence was allegedly committed on December 29 last year in Embakasi, Nairobi.Police records say Koti&rsquo;s sister blocked the tap which irritated the tenants, led by the complainant, who demanded to fetch water. It was further alleged that Koti was restrained by other neighbours after she attempted to hit Kerubo in her stomach. She then abused Kerubo and threatened to kill her baby, the prosecution says. Koti was released on Sh10,000 bail.